review.body:
- http://localhost:8080/packages/fiori/test/pages/SideNavigationOnly.html?sap-ui-theme=sap_fiori_3
    - 1. Select item “Home” and focus it
    - 2. Select item “People” and focus it
    - 3. Both focuses look different 
- In Fiori 3, the item “Local.......” truncates at the end of the div. In Horizon if this item is selected, the blue dot is too far to the right. The item should have 0.5rem padding-right.
- By design the sub-items should not have icons. We can remove them from the test pages and stories.
- In Horizon there should be a small gap between each item that changes based on Cozy/Compact. There is already a gap in Collapsed mode.
- A Disabled item should also have cursor: default. Right now, the text element inside it shows the text selection cursor because of cursor: auto.
- Collapse the SideNavigation and select the item “Home” after it is selected, press and hold it - the icon’s color will turn white. Most likely the background should be changing just like it changes on the first time you press to select the item.
- By definition the property `whole-item-toggleable` will make an item collapse/expand its items when you click anywhere on the item, not only on the icon. And additionally it is said that it will not fire the click event. However, I am still able to select this item with the keyboard and the click event fires. We can address this later as a separate issue.

review.body:
- http://localhost:8080/packages/fiori/test/pages/SideNavigationOnly.html?sap-ui-theme=sap_fiori_3
    - 1. Select item “Home” and focus it
    - 2. Select item “People” and focus it
    - 3. Both focuses look different 
- In Fiori 3, the item “Local.......” truncates at the end of the div. In Horizon if this item is selected, the blue dot is too far to the right. The item should have 0.5rem padding-right.
- By design the sub-items should not have icons. We can remove them from the test pages and stories.
- In Horizon there should be a small gap between each item that changes based on Cozy/Compact. There is already a gap in Collapsed mode.
- A Disabled item should also have cursor: default. Right now, the text element inside it shows the text selection cursor because of cursor: auto.
- Collapse the SideNavigation and select the item “Home” after it is selected, press and hold it - the icon’s color will turn white. Most likely the background should be changing just like it changes on the first time you press to select the item.
- By definition the property `whole-item-toggleable` will make an item collapse/expand its items when you click anywhere on the item, not only on the icon. And additionally it is said that it will not fire the click event. However, I am still able to select this item with the keyboard and the click event fires. We can address this later as a separate issue.
